---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import featherImg from "../assets/visuals/feather.png";
---

<section
  class="relative flex flex-col min-h-[120vh] py-48 px-6 bg-background items-center justify-center"
>
  <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="relative flex justify-center items-center h-full">
      <Image
        src={featherImg}
        alt="Feather"
        width={600}
        height={800}
        class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-[400px] sm:max-w-[500px] md:max-w-[600px]"
        loading="eager"
      />
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 z-0 bg-gradient-radial from-featherbg via-featherbg/60 to-transparent blur-2xl"
      ></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div
    class="relative z-20 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 max-w-5xl mt-20 text-text"
  >
    <div class="p-6 bg-surface/70 backdrop-blur-md rounded-xl shadow-lg">
      <h3 class="text-highlight text-lg font-bold mb-2">
        What is Nexla?
      </h3>
      <p>
        Nexla is a platform for managing creative attention â€” the one thing that can't be automated.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-surface/70 backdrop-blur-md rounded-xl shadow-lg">
      <h3 class="text-highlight text-lg font-bold mb-2">
        What does the name mean?
      </h3>
      <p>
        Nexla comes from the Aztec word for "tribute." It represents the power and scarcity of creative insight.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
